4 <!--75-->Goblin Scimitar<br />
4 <!--72-->Goblin Runner<br />
4 <!--73-->Goblin Scavengers<br />
2 <!--90-->Relics of Moria    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Ok, well i wanted to play something different than arwen/lego start with rangers and crap, so I figured start LoG and common Merry, Merry can be a good fighting force against moria minions(who else would they use? :)) and Boro is there to take hits with his armor. Ideal situation is to get Gandalf and Aragorn out first turn, gandalf is the man with the plan(ok, spells :P) and he can do some good work for ya, Aragorn is there to kill stuff, plain and simple. <br />
<br />
Conditions are horrendously powerful(both moria and sauron) so there is Sleep and Sentinels in there, to kill off all those nasty conditions. Rumil is in there both for Sentinels and to kill off some annoying orcs at an oppurtune time. ROTN is the best Aragorn there is, moria is just too strong to ignore, KiE would prove little to no healing anyways.<br />
<br />
For Shadow I went with Moria just because it&#39;s the best, Cave Troll Ownz J00. I play both the Hammer and Chain because it sucks to have your Troll machine gunned by Aragon/Lego and they can both be pulled with Relics. I chose not to play swarms because I wanted to keep the deck size down(76 cards is my magic number) and it really isn&#39;t as useful for me because I seem to always get hit with sentinels. Tower Assassin is there too kill of pesky Elrond/Ottar/Rumil/Galadriel or anyone else who seems to be annoying you :). Besides that it&#39;s pretty much what I would call standard Moria.<br />
<br />
